caption: Maybe I haven't bought the right dish yet, but the food here always seems to be just a little less delicious than I'm used to from Thai restaurants.  Once I ordered a fried fish dish expecting a good-sized filet, as I have experienced at other Thai places, and the dish had a pile of tiny pieces of fish surrounded by a lot of crunchy batter.  I basically "shelled" the fish from the batter to eat it. On a positive note, the roast duck curry is good.

Rayes our server was absolutely amazing and knowledgeable. If I could take him with me, I would have! The rest of the staff is just as good too. The food is flavorful and clean. The atmosphere is fun, modern and classy. Can't wait to go back!
Nice atmosphere!!

Came here twice since I found out about it, only separated by my day off. My new favorite place for lunch around here. Everything is reasonably priced. Nice size portions. The yum num, beef salad with lime, is awesome. Exactly what I expected. Red curry us so good. We'll be returning often. Only bad thing I can say is I ordered the beef with my curry and they gave me chicken, but it was still delicious. Hope y'all support this establishment. You won't regret it.
The food was absolutely delicious! Thank you for having us.
Got takeout from here and it was ready fast, tasted great, and wasn’t expensive. Nice staff, 100% would recommen
pad thai was great! super kind and friendly staff!
Is very good,  🙏 I am recommending that drink siam paradise.
Great food, good prices, friendly staff.

I honestly am pleasantly surprised by them! I order them Postmates pickup and got some sashimi and nigiri. Both are pretty good! I was initially a little hesitant because I was afraid that the quality of the fish was going to be bad because of the amazing price, but I took a gamble anyways (lol pandemic doesn’t help financially and I really wanted sushi.) granted, they are not like premium quality where they like melt in your mouth or taste like the fresh ocean, but they were pretty good and look delicious and clean. I would highly recommend it if you are just craving some sushi or raw fish but can’t pay a load for them!

Went to grab lunch near the Capitol One Arena. This place was so beautiful and the workers were so nice. It's sad how they got hit hard along with the rest of Chinatown because of the pandemic/racial unrest in DC. Please go and support these awesome people!
Friendly staff and delicious food!
Such great service and food! You can no go wrong eating here.
I adore this restaurant a lot. It has a unique ambiance. The cuisine is good. the service is powerful and the waiters are trained. The pay is decent. greatly recommend.
I only had drinks here, specifically patron margaritas. Delicious! Not too sour not too sweet. Get sugar on the brim..I prefer sweet.
I always arrive getting some food in here. I enjoy the efficient service and well made dishes. Keep up the good work.

Give this place some business! It is so good. After a long day, we sat on the patio and had a beer and some amazing Thai. The staff was super nice and my food disappeared. I meant to leave some to take home but ended up eating it all.

The BEST Thai in the neighborhood—hands down. It’s a family-run hole in the wall with fantastic food. It’s become our COVID comfort food place...and we make SURE to call rather than use delivery apps to make sure this great place stays afloat. Try the Pad See Euw, Pad Thai, or the garden rolls.

Pad Thai was disappointing. Very dry and not much flavor. There was really no sauce, no hint of fish sauce, no sesame oil, no cilantro, nothing. They did include a side of peanuts but no red pepper for spice. The chicken was very dry and tough. Even the fried egg placed on top (which was a little weird) was tough. I make much better at home and I am an old white dude.  NO trace of Thai in my family. I've eaten Pad Thai at many many places and this was at the very bottom of the list. The spring rolls were descent and had a good sauce which I ended up putting on the Pad Thai. I will not order it again. How can a Thai restaurant not have a great Pad Thai as their center piece? The owner should go to allrecepies.com and search for Pad Thai recipes for some help.
“Their Green curry is just the right amount of heat and slightly sweet.” -Me  “The peanut sauce on the house salad is delicious.” -My roommate
No bathroom for customers
I had a superb experience at this spot. We enjoyed the wonderful ambience and the meals. The staff members are super welcoming. I’m happy we eventually managed to try this place.
Worst pad Thai I have ever had in my life. The noodles  were a solid piece of dry noodles stuck in the container. I had to make my own pad Thai sauce to simply have it be edible. Awful experience.

Terrible food, terrible salad! I ordered pad thai, it was dry, the noodle flavor was terrible and the meat wasn’t even eatable! The thai salad came with spinach!!! What thai salad comes with spinach?? Also the sauce was wrong, and they used any random vegetable they had in the kitchen. Never try them again!
After a concert at Sixth & I, this restaurant was still open for carry-out! The food was delicious!
Fantastic spot to buy food when in a rush. Their customer service is prompt, pricing is reasonable, awesome ambience. Will come visit again

Great food and my drink, Lychee martini was GREAT!!

I've been to this Thai Restaurant a few times. The food is good. The decor is fine as well. Located in Chinatown DC it well located for adventures to the monuments. Prices are reasonable. Their service is standout, very quick, responsive, and courteous service is provided. A solid Thai food experience.  Traveler and Adventurer - IG @brian.dent
My team from comes here every Thursday and only ask for Biggke.  He defines excellent service! The food is also very good.  One of the best Thai food I have had in the DC/Northern VA/MD area.
Very good and fast.

The Tom Ka soup was great but the main dish looked like they just defrosted some frozen veggies with precooked chicken and dumped some garlic sauce on it. I had noodle dishes before that were allot better  though. The service was great but sub par quality main dish.
Tasty choices, not too pricey, waitstaffer was helpful in responding to my questions and concerns re spiciness of my meal. Glad I listened to him!
Popped in here unexpectedly. We got the crispy wings and wonton chicken. Sooooo good, the drinks aren’t the strongest but they serve their purpose.
This spot sure knows how to please their clients. Constantly with a welcoming demeanor. The food is reasonably priced, always fresh and clean.
Just finished a lovely lunch. The place was packed with locals both suits and blue collar. Waitstaff was efficient and portion size was huge.
Quick service, good food and a great price.
I had much better Thai food before..

It was very busy that day but the staff was excellent. We ordered dumplings for an appetizer and they were delicious. Very full dumplings, and a good sauce to go with then. The pad see ew and the drunken noodles were both delicious. Very hot and delicous. The thai coffee was also great. Not too sweet. Cant put over enough how good the service was.
The worst thai food I ever had in my life. How can you screw up Padthai. The beef i got was so tough i couldn't chew it. Just horrible.

Cute place. We came in on a Sunday night, at peak dinner time and it was that perfect level of busy where the noise didn't make it difficult to hear or be heard at all. It made the place feel busy and loved. We got our favorite staples of Thai food: the papaya salad was fantastic, the drunken noodles and green curry with veggies and tofu were pretty darn good. The veggie mix they used includes baby corn which I hate, but my husband likes, so neutral verdict there.  :)
I'm a Thai food fiend and have tried a lot of different Thai restaurants in DC. This was some of the worst Thai food I've had in the city. I was definitely disappointed.

last night was our first time we went to this fine restaurant. But It is surely not the last time. We had great time with the courteous service, with the fine  cuisine and wine and with the honest charge. We will absolutely visit there again.

I dine in this great restaurant  a lot! This is my favorite spot to eat.  I visit this place many times. The cooking is very good, the crew is polite and the payment is fair. I enjoy going in this spot over a good meal.

I went there to eat after coming from Metro Headquarter. I set down when there was hardly know one there and than she set someone right. Turned me comfortable to vexatious. So I couple bites and ask for takeout bag. But on the way out I saw somebody that worked Yumm's on South Capital Street S. E. . A person that I would never be around my food.

First Thai restaurant we visited during our stay in Washington DC. Staff is very friendly and responsive, and this is a Thai restaurant run by Thai folks. This place has a nice vibe, seating is a little tight but once you get settled in you feel right at home. Bar appears to be fitted nicely, but we ordered a single tap beer which was served cold. We ordered one basil fried rice with chicken and one basil with chicken and a fried egg. Portions were decent, and the spice levels were spot on (the fried rice was ordered as a 5 out of 10 level and was perfect). The rice used in the fried rice was softer than what I like, which means it was clumpy, where I prefer rice cooked with less water. Service was great, never ran out of water. Everything was clean and had a nice authentic Bangkok decor. Being Thai food snobs we reserve a perfect 5 stars for places that can also cook to authentic Thai tastes. For Farang taste you can’t go wrong here!
Great spot for a meal before Caps games.

I love Thai food so I have tried it out in different places and this place is still my favorite. I really like noodles in this place, specially,  drunken noodles, they are spicy but delicious, you can taste the fresh basil. Also try the Pad Thai with an ice Thai tea. The staff is friendly and efficient. I highly recommend this place.

Every time my friend and I come back we try something new.  Today we shared Absolute Thai Noodle and Tofu Gai Sub from the special lunch menu.  The portions are very large and the $11 cost includes an egg roll. With Thai iced tea, it was a bargain lunch for under $15.  For a couple of dollars more, there are lots of good choices on the regular menu.  We've always found the service good and the staff friendly.

Worst Thai food I ever! The worst worst thing is it was not every authentic. It was so bad that we ordered 2 dishes and couldn’t finish even one of them, still paid some $30 and also parking charges. Nothing could be bad than this.
The delicious food, on time service and warm hospitality makes up for the decor. I would recommend Absolute Thai if you’re looking to eat good Thai food! Definitely revisiting
Good food.
The best chicken wings I have ever tasted, I will definitely be taking people here and trying the rest of the menu.

This is a wonderful low-key Thai restaurant.  Friends have enjoyed the pad thai and panang curry.  I have really enjoyed the drunken noodles, thai street noodles (soup), and the pad see ew.  The appetizers are all generally very good.  I really like their wings--when we have gone with children, the chicken won-tons were a fan favorite.  The iced tea is a passion fruit tea and excellent in its unsweetened form, even for someone who grew up drinking sweet tea.  It gets crowded at lunch, but it seems like you can always find a table.  Dinner crowds some on the weekends, but during the week and on Sundays you can get the restaurant with just a few other people at dinner and enjoy a quieter more intimate experience.  This is one of my favorites that is in regular rotation for both personal and work lunches and dinners.

Worse customer service I've ever experienced from a restaurant owner. I simply didn't like what was prepared and literally had to argue to get my refund. Never going back. Other Thai restaurants ROCK.
Please avoid this place. This was the worst Thai food that I have had in my life:(
They accommodated our party of 15 with no problem, we were served promptly and respectfully, the food was delicious and the restaurant was clean. I would recommend

If you are looking for high prices, this isn't the right place.  If you are looking for something with lots of space around you, this isn't the right place either.  If you are looking for something that makes you feel special... keep looking.  However, if you are looking for good, simple Thai food where the value is high and the food is the main thing, not decor, not privacy then it will be hard to find a better place for basic Thai fare than this restaurant.  No regrets.  No doubts.  Will revisit often when in town.  Absolutely.

This was the some of the best Thai food I've had in a long time. The atmosphere is a little nicer than average, but you can come wearing jeans. There is patio seating, bar seating and plenty of tables. One thing odd about the bar is that your knees hit the bar before you can reach the table so that's a bit uncomfortable. Service was excellent and food was great. I ordered the Panang Curry which was very yummy and not too spicy. I'd like a little less peanut flavor in my Panang though. There was no parking, but that's expected with being in downtown. Loved it and will be back again.

The decor is not what wins you over here.  And the coffee is instant, as at most Thai restaurants. But the food is real tasty, and, as you would expect, there are lots of vegetarian options. The service is efficient!  At lunch, you may linger if you like, or you can be back to work inside an hour.

Knowing that the portions are large, we shared an order of Penang Curry and a starter of fried shrimp (delicious).  The staff were lovely and the prices reasonable.  Absolute Thai is now our go-to restaurant prior Shakespeare performances!

Delicious and large lunch portions. I got the Tom Yum Gai Sub Noodle Soup with veggie spring roll. My friends loved their meals too. Portions are so large we took leftover to go for another lunch. Atmosphere is nice and service is quick and friendly.

My regular order is tofu pad thai - no meat, no extra vegetables. Went there a couple of times and food was average/good enough. I was so grossed out. After I called back for a refund, which I got, the person on the other line offered to give me a coupon for my next visit. I didn't take it because I will not be back. Dine at your own risk.

I'd love to tell you how I felt about the food at this place, but we never made it that far. The ambience was nice and the waitstaff was polite, but when my co-worker tried to order a beer, they refused to recognize his Puerto Rican driver's license as a valid form of ID. Then they made the mistake of asking him for his passport to verify his age, because he obviously wasn't a citizen. Last I checked, while not a state, Puerto Rico is definitely part of the United States.  We're both old enough to have seen "Raiders of the Lost Ark" in theatres, and we have enough grey in our hair and our beards - so age verification could not have been an issue. We walked out and found another Thai restaurant down the street that did accept his ID.

This is a good Thai place. I will have to update this review. I am reviewing based off of 1 visit and 1 dish.  Drunken Noodle: I came during lunch. I ordered drunken noodle. I asked for Thai Spicy. I did not get Thai Spicy but it may be because of my extremely hot palette. The the vegetables were perfect. The noodles were also great. They are the thinner flat noodle versus the thick flat noodle that seem to be very hard to find in the DMV. My beef was good but it did not take much of the flavor from the sauce from the drunken noodle. Some of my pieces were tender while others were tough. The portions were perfect! I don't want the person reading this think that this place is not good because it is. I am giving it three stars because I have had other versions of drunken noodle that I like slightly better. Like I mentioned I love thick noodles. I also have a very spicy and salty palette. Maybe they were light on the dark soy sauce but the sauce seemed to sit in the back ground. I was expecting for it to be more prominent.  Customer Service: I was greeted when I came in. I was sat a table very quickly. My food came out in less than 5 minutes. My water was constantly being refilled. I was in and out very quickly. I was greeted on the way out as well! Customer service here is phenomenal!  I hope to come back and try their other dishes!
Great food! The bathroom could use some more cleaning, but decent place.

I love their green curry. Give me beef, give me chicken, it's doesn't matter, give me shrimp. Just mix it with green curry and out some rice on the side. The food here is so good. You would never look at this place and think I should eat there. The outside doesn't look like the inside. And the inside doesn't look like they would serve amazing food. But they do!! There was one surprise after another. And the staff is amazing as well. I go here all the time!
Some really great flavors and dishes here. Maybe steer clear of the pad thai. It was just okay. But I loved the soup.

Ordered dinner (7pm) for delivery, this is THE WORST Thai food i have ever had. I ordered fried rice & shrimp, pad Thai and rice and green curry. Everything was very dry and cold. The food was probably cooked 7 am. I’m guessing the good reviews here are probably from the employees.

I had just gotten into town and a friend of mine and I decided to look around and search for some Thai food. We found Absolute Thai conveniently located behind the Verizon Center. It was a busy Friday night for most of the restaurants on the 6th street. We luckily got a table at here before the whole dining room filled up. All three courses came out of the kitchen in an extremely timely manner. My highlight was the Chicken Pad Thai. My friend really enjoyed the fried tempura ice cream. He forced me to take a few bites because he was really loving it and said he would kick himself, if he ate the whole thing by himself. I have to say that was a great way to end the meal. The Thai Smile Martinis were delicious! I would definitely recommend one of those if you want to try a signature martini. If not, then they have Shock Top, which gets no complaints here!

Great food, quaint atmosphere and good service. My colleague and I came here for dinner during their HH so we ordered the deep fried beef strips and Thai fried chicken for appetizers. The beef was tasty (much better than I-Thai's) but the fried chicken was mediocre at best as it tasted like a normal frozen wings that they deep fried. For dinner I had the duck red curry and my colleague had the shrimp green curry. We asked for a 3/4 spice level and they delivered, quickly too! The food was well seasoned (no MSG, so they're not cheating!) with a generous portion. For the quality of food, portion and price this place easily worth the trip.

Standard Thai fare. Fresh flavors though a bit salty. Service is friendly, prices are reasonable.
Excellent Food. I have never had a bad meal here.  Good service with lots of room for improvement.
Great food & service. Plus you can sit outside and people watch!
affordable
Food is good and staff werent friendly when we went there
Food is great and drinks are fine. Service sucks. I'm still sitting here and it's been around 10 min with my napkin on my plate and nothing. Still waiting. .....
My friends and I all love this place! My favorite is the tom yum mushroom soup, which doesn't really exist anywhere else.
Absolute Thai is by far the best thai I've had in DC. Being from Seattle, I have found it difficult to find Thai food that can compare to the delicious fare in the PNW.

It's great if you're American and don't know much about Thai food. Not tasty or authentic. Absolute Thai...I guess they were being sarcastic  I asked for extra spicy Pad Thai and it was not spicy at all. On asking for it to be made spicier, I was asked to use the chili sauce and condiments  No Thai restaurant worth their repute would even *think* of saying something like that; it's a disgraceful thing to say. Like being told to put ketchup on a pizza  On sending it back, it came back with just added chili flakes. That's NOT how you make something spicier.  Save your money. Just pick up a Banh Mi between 7th and 6th on H
Bad service. Some metal thing in the rice. Very bad experience.
Great place! Food is simple, artfully presented, and delicious.
Authentic Thai! Great value lunch sets on weekdays.
the ingredients r not fresh.
Excellent food and service. Enjoyable atmosphere and people.

It was terrible! The food and also the service! I ordered fried rice but it was not fried rice It was too sticky and has terrible taste! It was not Thai food at all. And also they were very very bad at service. They gave us a bill including the tax with their bad service. I am really really angry with their attitude and food.

Very very terrible food!! Service was awful and  food wasn't like real thai food. It was really different when I ate in Thailand. I was so disappointed! !!!!!:( I will never go this restaurant again!!! Also they didn't give exact change . Please look carefully after they give change!

Did takeout but the restaurant was nice in an "authentic" way. Food was wonderful. I ordered the Ka-Prao ($13)  which is listed as a fairly spicy dish and it was definitely on the hotter side. Taste was excellent. I would say the amount of food was "fine",  but I would have preferred a just a little more for take out and $13 per dish. I would definitively go back again
Solid Thai food. The pad thai and drunken noodle are both solid, but nothing special.

A very good restaurant. I usually get drunken noodles or pad thai, and it's always done well. The prices are decent as well, especially for Chinatown, with good serving sizes. Their spicy hot levels are much spicier than normal Americanized restaurant fair, which is excellent. You always have the option of getting it non-spicy. You don't always get the option to go as spicy as they do.
Drunken Noodles were good, a little heavy on the noodles. The Tom Kha Ga was excellent.
Loved the food, ambience and service!!

The entrees were fine, although a little too sweet. The white rice, however, was mushy and disgusting; I could not even finish half of it. It seemed as though they put in way too much water and overcooked the rice to some extreme degree, or perhaps simply used rice that was no longer fresh. Either way, it was probably the single worst bowl of white rice I have ever had in my life... Sigh.
Had the Pad See Ew and was very good. Went for lunch and portion size and price was good. Definitely going back before an event at Verizon Center.
Fast lunch service
Their Red Curry, made "Thai Hot" was *actually* really hot, and wonderfully flavorful.  I loved every bite.
Service was good, but my Spicy Crispy Chicken was tastless, i haven't eaten in McDonald's in ages, but i imagine chicken mcnugets have more flavour
Terrible!! Frozen vegetables!! Really???
Love this place... everything is so good and reasonably priced considering the area.

For someone who loves Thai food, this is pretty mediocre. However the Thai tea was delicious. For an American who isn't into Thai food, this place is certainly adequate. Service was good and the restaurant itself was nice inside.
Great vegetables and great salmon
The food was fantastic!  The duck with the red curry was gorgeous,  and the chicken fried rice was gobbled up by my 8 and 6 year old. Chicken wings app is a must!
Great modern atmosphere with equally great food!
Awesome experience.
The food was awesome but, it was very slow.
Amazing green winton soup.

Great PadThai, but ask for mild if you don't like a kick to it. Drunken Noodles are good too. Directly across from the Verizon Center, and practically empty before Caps games. Reasonable prices considering the location.

Came here with my family, it was excellent. We were seated and served quickly, the staff was very courteous and helpful, and the food was delicious. I'll be returning next time I'm in town. Great value for the price (relatively inexpensive).
Good food and good service. I would go back.

Nice sized portions. Had an authentic, healthy, and specialty sides of the menu to order. We had the Thai Fried Rice and Healthy Green Curry. Both were tasty and met my expectations. Not the best but good and inexpensive.

I came here after visiting the Newseum because it was a short walk (10 minutes).  The food is reasonably priced, decor is nice, and the staff is friendly and attentive.  Although their menu did not have as much variety as many Thai restaurants I have been to, the Pad Thai and Massaman Curry exceeded my expectations.  I also liked that they had a "healthy section" of their menu and a fairly large dessert menu.  I would definitely come back again!

This place is great. I've been back so far 3 times and counting. And each time I've gone with different friends.  Conviently located on the side of the Verizon Ctr. It's a nice hole in the wall retreat.  I would recommend this place.
Lovely service, tasty food, appropriate portions, average décor--a touch homely in places. I would def recommend. Families would be at home and are welcome.
Absolutely wonderful! Food is great... Service is too. Its not much on the outside but don't let that fool you.
Good food and great on price. Service was very good too!
Service was great, food was spicy and awesome

Friday afternoon lunch wasn't crowded at all, which was a good thing.  The waiter, his name was Get (had a funky hairstyle), was awesome and very helpful.  He was from Thailand and gave us some traditional cooking methods on how to make the tom yum soup and pad thai.  The pad thai was very very good, better than thaitanic.  The noodles are better tasting and they put the egg on top of the noodles. Overall a great experience.  The location is a little rundown, but should get better as time goes.
